events.name: New York Knicks at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Terrence Ross scored 18 of his season-high 30 points in the second half, and the Orlando Magic used a decisive third-quarter run to beat the New York Knicks 107-89 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ross scores season-high 30, Magic rally past Knicks 107-89

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 40 points and eight assists, and the Atlanta Hawks snapped a four-game losing streak with a 122-114 victory over the Boston Celtics on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 40, Hawks end skid, slip by Celtics 122-114

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 31 points, 11 rebounds and nine assists and hit a key jumper late to help the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Houston Rockets 118-113 on Wednesday night.

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: - Bradley Beal made two free throws with a tenth of a second left to give the Washington Wizards their third straight victory, 130-128 over the Denver Nuggets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal hits late free throws, Wizards edge Nuggets 130-128

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 36 points, 17 rebounds and 10 rebounds, and Malcolm Brogdon added 32 points and nine rebounds as the Indiana Pacers beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 134-128 in overtime on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis, Brogdon lead Pacers past Timberwolves 134-128 in OT

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 37 points and the Chicago Bulls beat the Detroit Pistons 105-102 Wednesday night on short notice.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine leads Bulls over Pistons in newly scheduled game

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored 43 points, including a go-ahead three-point play with 16.5 seconds left, to lift the Portland Trail Blazers to their sixth consecutive victory, 126-124 over the New Orleans Pelicans on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard has 43, go-ahead score as Blazers edge Pelicans

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Grayson Allen and Jonas Valanciunas each scored 22 points and Ja Morant posted his first triple-double of the season as the Memphis Grizzlies defeated the Oklahoma City Thunder 122-113 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Allen,  Valanciunas lead Grizzlies past Thunder 122-113

events.name: Miami Heat at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry made a go-ahead 3-pointer with 1:15 left in overtime, set up Andrew Wiggins for one the next time down before delivering a final dagger from deep, leading the Golden State Warriors to a 120-112 victory over the Miami Heat on Wednesday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry and his supporting cast rally Warriors past Heat in OT

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 24 points, Rudy Gobert had 23 points and 20 rebounds, and the Utah Jazz rolled past the short-handed Los Angeles Clippers 114-96 on Wednesday night for their ninth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz beat short-handed Clips 114-96 for 9th straight win
